gumfield
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:
Definition:the land in North Auckland where fossil kauri gum could be found (often pl on analogy of goldfield(s).)
Origin: [none]
Register: historical
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: cf.(gum)digging, (gum)diggings
